		   <br /><nobr><span id="notbold">Score</span>: Good [3.93]</nobr><br /><br /><a href="/cgi-bin/pm.pl?action=addtolist&addname=Aarenla&type=Address" id="fs8"><img src="/shared/plus.gif" border="0" align="middle" height="9" width="9" alt="Add to address book"> Add to address book</a><br /><img src="/shared/transp.gif" width="135" border="0" height="1"></td><td valign="top" class="mform2" width="100%"><p>I wouldn't reccomend doing any AA whatsoever at 51. AA xp is set up so that you gain xp like at 51st level. This means for you to gain one AA point it is going to take you the same amount of time as it would take you to level from 51 - 52.<br>Now if you wait until after 55 or so to even start AA xp it comes faster. The AA is still set up for you to earn xp on the 51st level. The only difference is that you are killing level 55 mobs now. So imagine how fast the xp would come if at 51 you could just run around killing reds all day, well this is almost the same as getting AA xp at 55.<br>Alot of people want to rush into AA so they can run around with a baron tag over thier head. I say fine, let em. You run around with a baron tag at 51 while I get about 4 more levels on me and get my 6 AA for baron in probably the same amount of time it took you even to reach baron.</p><br /><span class="sm">----------------------------</span><br />Of his knowledge a man should never boast,<br>Rather be sparing of speach<br>When to his house a wiser comes:<br>Seldom do those who are silent make mistakes;<br>Mother wit is ever a faithful freind.</td></td></tr><tr><td colspan="2" class="mform2"><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" width="100%"><tr><td id="fs8"></td><td align="right" id="fs8" >1 Replies</td></tr></table>
